Products.FullDescription: Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen Pork & Chive Dumplings
Products.RichDescription:
Our Pork & Chive Dumplings feature our original recipe of fresh, Australian pork, chopped chives, shallots, onions and crushed garlic – all wrapped within a super thin dumpling pastry. Simply steam, boil or pan-fry for minutes and the dumplings are ready!

Each bite is bursting with flavour and juiciness. We follow the Cantonese style of cooking of only adding condiments to bring out the natural, full-bodied flavours of the ingredients. Most frozen dumplings on the market are packed raw and need to be carefully cooked. Our Pork & Chive Dumplings are fully cooked before being packed and stay fresher for longer. For a hassle-free and easy meal, simply place them in the steamer or boil them with your favourite noodle soup for a delicious and nutritious meal with over 10 grams of protein per serving!

Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen has been proudly making Dim Sum in Australia since 1982. Our vision is to maintain and promote the integrity of authentic Dim Sum for all families to enjoy.

Our Siu Mai recipe is a timeless Yum Cha classic. Each Siu Mai is made from diced pork shoulder, plump prawns and shiitake mushrooms, wrapped in a super thin dumpling pastry. Simply steam for 7 minutes and the Siu Mai are ready!

The bite-sized portion of each Siu Mai makes them the perfect choice for entertaining friends at your next get together with minimal fuss and effort. Sure to impress and having your guests asking for more, each bite is chunky and bursting with flavour and umami.  What was once only found in a bamboo steamer at a Yum Cha restaurant can now be enjoyed from the convenience of your home. Having a quiet night in? Steam a plate of Siu Mai all for yourself and nibble away at a good source of protein with over 11 grams per serving!

Hong Kong Dim Sim Kitchen has been proudly making Dim Sum in Australia since 1982. Our vision is to maintain and promote the integrity of authentic Dim Sum for all families to enjoy.
